abstract: >-
  Supplementary materials, data, and software for the pilot study "Constrained
  vs. Unconstrained Free-Fall and Projectile-Motion AI Problem-to-Simulation
  Generation." The study compares constrained NewtonSimAI simulations (GPT-4o-mini
  extraction into a fixed framework) with unconstrained Claude Opus 4.6
  generations across five Force Concept Inventory questions, one generation per
  question per condition, scored against a 17-criterion technical and physical
  accuracy rubric. The archive contains the reported summary scores, a derived
  criterion-level scoring file (reconstructed from the reported summary and the
  rubric, not an original contemporaneous scoring sheet), the unconstrained
  simulation artifacts, the NewtonSimAI source code, prompts, and research
  documentation. Original source code is MIT-licensed; original data and
  documentation are CC BY 4.0. Force Concept Inventory materials are third-party
  and are not redistributed.
